JUDIAgent
=========

JUDIAgent is maintained as a research codebase for retrieval-grounded Julia/JUDI
scientific coding agents.

Provenance and third-party material:

- Early repository scaffolding was informed by JutulGPT:
  https://github.com/SINTEF-agentlab/JutulGPT
  JUDIAgent has since been reorganized around JUDI.jl seismic workflows,
  dual-stage validation, domain-quality review, and task-aware metric guidance.
  The upstream JutulGPT MIT copyright notice is preserved in `LICENSE`; the
  JUDIAgent modifications are attributed to Georgia Institute of Technology.

- The retrieval corpus under `src/judiagent/rag/judi/` includes JUDI.jl
  documentation and examples used as grounding material for generation and
  validation. JUDI.jl is developed by the SLIM group and contributors:
  https://github.com/slimgroup/JUDI.jl

- JUDI.jl is distributed under the MIT License. Keep upstream copyright,
  author, citation, and license notices when redistributing substantial
  portions of its documentation, examples, or data-facing scripts.

